OL,3,CEngland's driest start to spring in 69
OL,4,Cyears raises risk of summer drought
OL,6,FEngland could be facing a summer
OL,7,Fdrought after suffering its driest
OL,8,Fstart to spring in 69 years, with
OL,9,Freservoirs low and farmers struggling
OL,10,Fto grow crops.
OL,12,FWater companies are under pressure to
OL,13,Fcut leaks and help customers save
OL,14,Fwater, as the Environment Agency warns
OL,15,Fof a "medium" risk of drought this
OL,16,Fsummer.
OL,18,FWhile no hosepipe bans are currently
OL,19,Fplanned, the agency said restrictions
OL,20,Fcould be introduced in the coming
OL,21,Fmonths if dry conditions continue.
