OL,3,CEngland's driest start to spring in 69
OL,4,Cyears raises risk of summer drought
OL,6,FThe warning comes ahead of a meeting
OL,7,Fof the government's national drought
OL,8,Fgroup on Wednesday, involving
OL,9,Fministers, officials, water firms and
OL,10,Fenvironmental groups.
OL,12,FEngland has had its driest start to
OL,13,Fspring since 1956, with just half the
OL,14,Fusual rainfall recorded in April and
OL,15,Fonly a quarter in March. Met Office
OL,16,Ffigures show April was also the
OL,17,Fsunniest on record for the UK.
OL,19,FReservoir levels in England now
OL,20,Faverage 84% full, down from 90% at the
OL,21,Fsame time in the drought year of 2022.
