OL,3,CEngland's driest start to spring in 69
OL,4,Cyears raises risk of summer drought
OL,6,FLevels are especially low in the north
OL,7,Feast and north west, where rainfall
OL,8,Fhas been the lowest since 1929.
OL,9,FFarmers are already irrigating crops,
OL,10,Fputting extra pressure on water
OL,11,Fsupplies.
OL,13,FRiver flows are also lower than usual
OL,14,Fin northern and central England, and
OL,15,Fwildfires have broken out in Cumbria,
OL,16,FDerbyshire and Dorset due to dry
OL,17,Fvegetation.
OL,19,FThe UK has swung between weather
OL,20,Fextremes in recent years, from
OL,21,Fdroughts and wildfires to floods.
