OL,3,CEngland's driest start to spring in 69
OL,4,Cyears raises risk of summer drought
OL,6,F"The dry conditions and lack of any
OL,7,Fsubstantial rainfall has meant farmers
OL,8,Fin some parts of the country have
OL,9,Fstarted to irrigate crops much earlier
OL,10,Fthan normal ` thankfully reservoirs
OL,11,Fare currently full following the wet
OL,12,Fautumn and winter."
OL,14,FUrging the government to recognise
OL,15,Fwater for food production, she added:
OL,16,F"The extreme weather patterns we have
OL,17,Fexperienced over the past few years is
OL,18,Fimpacting our ability to feed the
OL,19,Fnation.
